    <!-- Answer Writing Tips -->
    <div class="card article-body">
      <h2>Mains Answer Writing Strategy</h2>
      <h3>The 150-Word Answer (10 marks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Introduction (1-2 lines):</strong> Define the concept or state the context</li>
        <li><strong>Body (8-10 lines):</strong> 3-4 points with examples, data, or case studies</li>
        <li><strong>Conclusion (1-2 lines):</strong> Way forward or balanced assessment</li>
        <li><strong>Time:</strong> 7-8 minutes per answer</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>The 250-Word Answer (15 marks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Introduction (2-3 lines):</strong> Context + define the issue</li>
        <li><strong>Body (15-18 lines):</strong> Multiple dimensions — economic, social, political, environmental</li>
        <li><strong>Diagram/Flowchart:</strong> Add one if relevant (saves words, scores marks)</li>
        <li><strong>Conclusion (2-3 lines):</strong> Balanced view + way forward</li>
        <li><strong>Time:</strong> 12-13 minutes per answer</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Golden Rules</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Use <strong>current affairs examples</strong> in every answer — read <a href="https://ujiyari.com/editorials/" target="_blank">Ujiyari editorials</a> daily</li>
        <li>Underline keywords — examiners scan fast</li>
        <li>Start each point on a new line — visual clarity matters</li>
        <li>Never leave a question unanswered — write something, even 3 points</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

